olive oil
½ Onion
¼ cup white wine vinegar
1 punnet cherry tomatoes
½ bag coriander
1 cucumber
½ bag mint
2 clove garlic
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 tin chickpeas
1 carrot
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet coconut milk
1 packet chicken breast

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Cut onion in half. Thinly slice half the onion and finely chop the remaining onion (this will be used in step 5!).
• In a small bowl, combine the white wine vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt. Scrunch the sliced onion in your hands, then add
to the pickling liquid with just enough water to cover the onion. Stir to coat and set aside.

• Finely chop tomato, cucumber and coriander. Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine tomato, cucumber and coriander. Set aside.
• Pick and thinly slice mint leaves (see ingredients). Finely chop garlic. Cut mini flour tortillas into wedges. Drain and rinse chickpeas. Grate the carrot.

• In a second small bowl, combine mint, Greek-style yoghurt and a small drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

• Place the tortilla wedges on a lined oven tray. Drizzle (or spray) with olive oil, season and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until
golden, 8-10 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.
TIP: Keep an eye on them. You want them crisp, but not burnt!

 • While the tortillas are baking, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, carrot and remaining onion, tossing occasionally, until cooked through, 3-4 minutes.
• Add chickpeas and cook until heated through, 2 minutes.
• Add garlic and Mumbai spice blend and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Stir through tomato paste and coconut milk, then season generously. Simmer until sauce has thickened, 2-3 minutes.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture seems dry.

• Drain pickled onion.
• Divide tortilla chips between bowls. Top with coconut-chickpea mixture, cucumber salsa and pickled onion.
• Serve with mint yoghurt. Enjoy!

TIP: Serve the tortilla chips on the side if you prefer!